# 🔩 Components List — Smart Plant Irrigation System

## 1. Microcontroller & Development

- **1×** ESP32 NodeMCU Development Board (Model: ESP32-WROOM-32)
  - Firmware mapping: ADC1 channels (GPIO 32, 33, 34) + digital GPIOs (14, 25, 26, 27)
- **1×** USB cable (Micro-USB or USB-C, depending on board) for firmware flashing

## 2. Sensors, Actuators & Tubing

- **3×** Submersible mini water pumps (Brand: RUNCCI-YUN)
  - Specs: DC 3V–5V/6V, brushless motor
- **1×** 4-channel 5V relay module (Brand: AZDelivery)
  - Specs: Optoisolated, Low-Level-Trigger activation. Only 3 of the 4 channels are used to drive the pumps.
- **3×** Resistive soil moisture sensors / hygrometers (Brand: AZ-Delivery)
  - Specs: Fork-type resistive probes with signal conditioning board.
  - Powered in parallel via a single GPIO pin (`SENSOR_POWER_PIN`), activated only during readings to prevent corrosion.
  - *(Purchased as a 5-piece pack: 3 in use, 2 spare)*
- **1×** Flexible PVC tubing, 3m total
  - To be cut into 3 sections to connect the pumps to the pots

## 3. Power Management & Power Modules

- **1×** 4×AA battery holder with ON/OFF switch
  - Specs: Holds 4× AA batteries (nominal voltage: 6V with alkaline / 4.8V with NiMH rechargeable)
- **1×** Adjustable DC-DC buck step-down converter (Brand: RUNCCI-YUN / Model: ANGEEK XL4016E1)
  - Specs: Accepts 4–38V input, regulated output set to a stable 5V for the relay module and pumps
